<section id="Organising">

	<h2>Header cards</h2>

	<p>Sometimes it can be useful to split up long lists with header cards. Header cards are styled to look just like Trello list headers. To make a header card, start your card text with one or more hash symbols (<kbd class="tag">#</kbd> — make sure you leave a space after the hash); or two or more dashes (<kbd class="tag">--</kbd>); or forward slashes (<kbd class="tag">//</kbd>). Symbols at the beginning and end of the title will be stripped.</p>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="EnableHeaderCards" name="EnableHeaderCards">
			<label for="EnableHeaderCards">
				Header cards
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Enable header cards</p>
			<p>Default: off</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="HeaderCardsExtraSpace" name="HeaderCardsExtraSpace">
			<label for="HeaderCardsExtraSpace">
				Extra space
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Add extra space above header cards</p>
			<p>A little extra space can make header cards stand out better</p>
			<p>Default: off</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Separator cards</h2>

	<p>Separator cards create a blank gap between cards. You can use stickers on separator cards, but all other card content is hidden. To make a separator card, type two or more line symbols in a row, then no other text. Line symbols are dashes (<kbd class="tag">--</kbd>), equals signs (<kbd class="tag">==</kbd>) or underscores (<kbd class="tag">__</kbd>):</p>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="EnableSeparatorCards" name="EnableSeparatorCards">
			<label for="EnableSeparatorCards">
				Separator cards
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Enable separator cards</p>
			<p>Default: off</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="SeparatorCardsVisibleLine" name="SeparatorCardsVisibleLine">
			<label for="SeparatorCardsVisibleLine">
				Horizontal rule
			</label>
		</option-widget>
		<div>
			<p>Show separators as a visible line</p>
			<p>Default: off</p>
		</div>
	</div>

</section>
